run tests in any browser that supports HTML5 (including IE9+, Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Opera).  OS 
agnostic - run tests on Win, Mac or Linux.  Run tests on remote computers and mobile devices, in 
multiple browsers and on multiple machines simultaneously, or headless.  Provides wrapper-free access to 
DOM via jQuery or a browser's API - does not require WebDriver or other tools.  Ships with 
powerful built-in visual test recorder, and can execute generated tests on demand or as 
part of a CI system.  Tests can be edited or written with the provided IDE in JavaScript and TypeScript. 
</p>

